This paper is about recommendation systems, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of Word2Vec, a natural language processing technique, in recommendation systems also makes it relevant to the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with data management and analysis, which is relevant to the subfield of database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the use of non-textual features, which can be considered as a form of feature engineering, making it relevant to the subfield of information science (cs.SI).
